I think it can be good to have a centralized list with all supported estimators. It should provide:

* estimator name, a link to the original docs for the estimator;
* a link to additional parameters eli5.explain.. / eli5.show.. functions take for the estimator, and/or a link to the function which actually explains weights or predictions;
* a brief description of the explanation method, with a link to a more detailed description.

I think sklearn.tree, sklearn.ensemble and xgboost support deserves its own tutorial. It should show examples for all of them and explain how to interpret the results:

* what do feature importances mean (in case of sklearn: what's Gini Importance; see also: https://github.com/glouppe/phd-thesis);
* how to interpret graphviz and text output for a single decision tree;
* how we explain xgboost, RandomForest.., Gradientboosting..., ExtraTrees... predictions.
